    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a challenging slate today, but the optimizer remains locked on **Yordan Alvarez** as our unequivocal anchor. With an elite efficiency score of 87.42, **Yordan Alvarez** is primed for a massive day against Bassitt, bolstered by a significant +16% park adjustment and a stellar BvP track record (26 PA), which elevates his base projection to near-elite status. Joining him as a priority start is **Colt Keith**, whose favorable matchup against Elder (4.29 xERA) and a high-leverage spot in the #3 hole earns him a strong 63.34 rating. While **Kazuma Okamoto** sits at a solid 60.36, we are monitoring his lineup status closely; if he slips out of the #4 spot, we may need to reassess his utility.\n\nStrategic risks abound today, specifically regarding **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber**, both of whom are facing the formidable Logan Webb (3.14 xERA). While **Trea Turner** remains in our starting lineup with a 53.93 score\u2014largely buoyed by the aggressive expectation that Webb\u2019s slow delivery will yield stolen base opportunities\u2014we are tempering expectations due to the elite pitcher penalty. **Kyle Schwarber** (50.54) also faces that Webb tax, though his elite xwOBA keeps him just above our \"Marginal\" threshold. We ultimately opted to bench **Jerar Encarnacion** (39.39), who was the most difficult exclusion of the day. Despite a decent platoon edge against S\u00e1nchez, his spot in the #8 hole suppressed his ceiling, leaving him just short of our 40.0 efficiency floor. As we monitor the rest of the bench\u2014including **Junior Caminero**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Caleb Durbin**\u2014we remain disciplined in our game-cap management, ensuring that roster depth like **Christian Yelich**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Gary Sanchez**, **Luke Raley**, **Josh Smith**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** are utilized only when the daily metrics justify the burn.",
